'''David Sutton''' (born 1966) is the current editor of the ''[[Fortean Times]]'' magazine. Sutton was born in [[Canterbury]], [[Kent]]. He was educated at the [[University of East Anglia]], [[University College London]], [[Birkbeck, University of London|Birkbeck College]] and the [[British Film Institute]]. He holds a doctorate, earned for his thesis on the origins and progress of [[British film]] [[comedy]], and is the author of the book ''A Chorus of Raspberries: British Film Comedy, 1929-1939''.<ref name="Mather2006">{{cite book|last=Mather|first=Nigel|title=Tears of laughter: comedy-drama in 1990s British cinema|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3yO3LY2QT2MC&pg=PA9|accessdate=29 September 2010|year=2006|publisher=Manchester University Press|isbn=978-0-7190-7077-8|page=9}}</ref>
